data.flavorText: The larger pair protects the little ones during battles. When facing strong opponents, the whole group will join the fight.

data.name: Cyclizar

attacks.name: Touring
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

data.flavorText: It can sprint at over 70 mph while carrying a human. The rider's body heat warms Cyclizar's back and lifts the Pokémon's spirit.

data.name: Cyclizar

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.

data.name: Flamigo

attacks.name: Nosedive
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: Thanks to a behavior of theirs known as "synchronizing," an entire flock of these Pokémon can attack simultaneously in perfect harmony.

data.flavorText: Dolliv shares its tasty, fresh-scented oil with others. This species has coexisted with humans since times long gone.

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: The thread it secretes from its rear is as strong as wire. The secret behind the thread's strength is the topic of ongoing research.

data.name: Toedscool

attacks.name: Furious Kicks
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.

attacks.name: Flame Cannon
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

data.flavorText: Armarouge evolved through the use of a set of armor that belonged to a distinguished warrior. This Pokémon is incredibly loyal.

attacks.name: Super Spicy Breath

data.flavorText: The green head has turned vicious due to the spicy chemicals stimulating its brain. Once it goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it.

data.name: Wiglett

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.

data.name: Slowpoke

attacks.name: Rest
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Asleep. Heal 30 damage from it.

data.flavorText: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.

data.name: Clauncher
data.flavorText: Clauncher's claws will regrow if they fall off. The meat inside the claws is edible, but it has a distinct flavor that doesn't appeal to all tastes.

attacks.name: Electro Paws
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Pawmot's fluffy fur acts as a battery. It can store the same amount of electricity as an electric car.

attacks.name: Everyone Discharge
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Lightning Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness.

attacks.name: Forced Sleep
attacks.text: Your opponent chooses 1 of their Benched Pokémon and switches it with their Active Pokémon. The new Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

data.flavorText: When it twitches its nose, it can tell where someone is sleeping and what that person is dreaming about.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon is a glutton, but it's bad at getting food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.

data.name: Greavard

attacks.name: Graveyard Gamboling

data.flavorText: This friendly Pokémon doesn't like being alone. Pay it even the slightest bit of attention, and it will follow you forever.

data.name: Riolu

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.

data.name: Ralts
data.flavorText: The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people's emotions.

data.name: Kirlia

attacks.name: Psychic

data.flavorText: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

data.name: Fidough

attacks.name: Springy
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: This Pokémon is smooth and moist to the touch. Yeast in Fidough's breath induces fermentation in the Pokémon's vicinity.

data.name: Klawf

attacks.name: Adrenaline Hammer
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Confused.

data.flavorText: Klawf hangs upside-down from cliffs, waiting for prey. But Klawf can't remain in this position for long because its blood rushes to its head.

attacks.name: Wild Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: Mabosstiff loves playing with children. Though usually gentle, it takes on an intimidating look when protecting its family.

data.name: Sandile
data.flavorText: It submerges itself in sand and moves as if swimming. This wise behavior keeps its enemies from finding it and maintains its temperature.

attacks.name: Clutch

abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon ex and Pokémon V.

attacks.name: Ghost Eye
attacks.text: Put 7 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon lives in dark places untouched by sunlight. When it appears before humans, it hides itself under a cloth that resembles a Pikachu.

data.name: Primeape

attacks.name: Pummel
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

data.flavorText: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.

data.name: Sudowoodo

attacks.name: Hit and Hide
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation.

data.name: Larvitar

attacks.name: Double Stab
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: Born deep underground, this Pokémon becomes a pupa after eating enough dirt to make a mountain.

data.name: Makuhita
data.flavorText: It grows stronger by enduring harsh training. It is a gutsy Pokémon that can withstand any attack.

data.name: Voltorb
data.flavorText: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

data.name: Electrode
data.flavorText: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

data.name: Bellibolt ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Jumping Press
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Paralyzing Ball
attacks.text: You may discard 2 Lightning Energy from this Pokémon to make your opponent's Active Pokémon Paralyzed.

data.name: Kilowattrel

attacks.name: Jet Wing
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

data.flavorText: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokémon can fly over 430 miles in a day.

data.name: Slowking ex
rules: Tera: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Profound Knowledge
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Wise Headbutt
attacks.text: You may search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.name: Gothita

attacks.name: Eerie Wave
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon is normally very innocent. When it is staring at something invisible, it is unblinking and utterly silent.

data.name: Oranguru

attacks.name: Plotter's Command
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't use that attack.

data.flavorText: People used to mistake Oranguru for a human when they saw it issue command after command to the other Pokémon of the forest.

data.name: Sandygast
data.flavorText: If it loses its shovel, it will stick something else— like a branch—in its head to make do until it finds another shovel.

data.name: Tinkatink

attacks.name: Scrap Pickup
attacks.text: Put an Item card from your discard pile into your hand.

data.flavorText: It swings its handmade hammer around to protect itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokémon that eat metal.

data.name: Tinkatink

attacks.name: Brutal Swing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

data.flavorText: It swings its handmade hammer around to protect itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokémon that eat metal.

data.name: Tinkaton

abilities.name: Gather Materials
abilities.text: You must discard a card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 3 cards.

attacks.name: Special Hammer
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any Special Energy attached, this attack does 90 more damage.

data.flavorText: This intelligent Pokémon has a very daring disposition. It knocks rocks into the sky with its hammer, aiming for flying Corviknight.

data.name: Paldean Tauros

attacks.name: Raging Horns
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Combat Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: This kind of Tauros, known as the Combat Breed, is distinguished by its thick, powerful muscles and its fierce disposition.

data.name: Pupitar
data.flavorText: This pupa flies around wildly by venting with great force the gas pressurized inside its body.

data.name: Shinx

abilities.name: Big Roar
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

data.name: Luxio
data.flavorText: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

data.name: Luxray

abilities.name: Swelling Flash
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in your hand and you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent, you may put this Pokémon onto your Bench.

attacks.name: Wild Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: It can see clearly through walls to track down its prey and seek its lost young.

data.name: Pincurchin

attacks.name: Needle Crush
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon generates electricity when it digests food. It uses its five hard teeth to scrape seaweed off surfaces and eat it.

data.name: Wattrel

attacks.name: United Wings
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile that has the United Wings attack.

data.flavorText: When its wings catch the wind, the bones within produce electricity. This Pokémon dives into the ocean, catching prey by electrocuting them.

data.name: Slowpoke

attacks.name: Tail-Fishing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. If tails, discard a card from your hand.

data.flavorText: It is incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

data.name: Mismagius

abilities.name: Magical Flick
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon to 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Its cry sounds like an incantation. It is said the cry may rarely be imbued with happiness-giving power.

data.name: Palossand

attacks.name: Earthen Power
attacks.text: If you have a Stadium in play, this attack does 80 more damage.

data.flavorText: The terrifying Palossand drags smaller Pokémon into its sandy body. Once its victims are trapped, it drains them of their vitality whenever it pleases.

data.name: Ceruledge

attacks.name: Life Sucker
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fighting Sword
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex or Pokémon V, this attack does 100 more damage.

data.flavorText: The fiery blades on its arms burn fiercely with the lingering resentment of a sword wielder who fell before accomplishing their goal.

data.name: Rabsca

attacks.name: Revival Blessing
attacks.text: Put a Pokémon from your discard pile onto your Bench.

attacks.name: Psybeam
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

data.flavorText: The body that supports the ball barely moves. Therefore, it is thought that the true body of this Pokémon is actually inside the ball.

data.name: Tinkatink

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

data.flavorText: It swings its handmade hammer around to protect itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokémon that eat metal.

data.name: Lycanroc ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Scary Fangs
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if it is Knocked Out), put 10 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

data.name: Rockruff
data.flavorText: This Pokémon is very friendly when it's young. Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures, but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

data.name: Hariyama

abilities.name: Arm Thrust Practice
abilities.text: All of your Pokémon take 10 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: It loves challenging others to tests of strength. It has the power to stop a train with a slap.

data.name: Croagunk

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

data.flavorText: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

data.name: Toxicroak

attacks.name: Knuckle Claws
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

data.flavorText: Swaying and dodging the attacks of its foes, it weaves its flexible body in close, then lunges out with its poisonous claws.

data.name: Passimian

attacks.name: Make the Assist
attacks.text: Move an Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon battles by throwing hard berries. It won't obey a Trainer who throws Poké Balls without skill.

data.name: Falinks

attacks.name: Reckless Charge Together
attacks.text: If Falinks is on your Bench, this attack does 90 more damage.

data.flavorText: The brass, which is the one that stands at the front and issues orders, is the strongest and smartest of the six.

data.name: Nacli
data.flavorText: It was born in a layer of rock salt deep under the earth. This species was particularly treasured in the old days, as they would share precious salt.

data.name: Nacli

attacks.name: Salt Coating
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It was born in a layer of rock salt deep under the earth. This species was particularly treasured in the old days, as they would share precious salt.

data.name: Garganacl

abilities.name: Blessed Salt
abilities.text: During Pokémon Checkup, heal 20 damage from each of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Knocking Hammer
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

data.flavorText: Garganacl will rub its fingertips together and sprinkle injured Pokémon with salt. Even severe wounds will promptly heal afterward.

data.name: Paldean Wooper
data.flavorText: After losing a territorial struggle, Wooper began living on land. The Pokémon changed over time, developing a poisonous film to protect its body.

data.name: Murkrow

attacks.name: Spin Turn
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: United Wings
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile that has the United Wings attack.

data.flavorText: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

data.name: Honchkrow

attacks.name: Dirty Throw
attacks.text: Discard a card from your hand. If you can't, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never forgives the mistakes of its Murkrow followers.
